            ; she said they were her own.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17740413-33-person324">
                  Dennis
               <interp inst="t17740413-33-person324" type="given" value="Dennis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17740413-33-person324" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             M'Donald. I am a constable: I went to Platt's lodgings, and found twelve pair of shoes and eight pieces of callimanco.</p>
               <p>Platt's Defence.</p>
               <p>My wife was lying-in; I was distressed for money, and sent Elder, who was nursing my wife at the time, to pawn them for me; she is innocent of it.</p>
               <p>The prisoner, Platt, called four witnesses to his character.</p>
               <p>PLATT <rs id="t17740413-33-verdict161" type="verdictDescription">
